"v.妨碍；减速 【英】 v. 妨碍，减速(to slow down; impede) 【考】 divert : shunt / retard : brake(转轨是用来转向/刹 车是用来减速)反义词: speed up(加速); accelerate(加速); expedite(促进); catalyze(促进); precipitate (加速) 【记】 re(使)+tard(迟缓)→ 使…迟缓→妨碍 【同】 同根词：tardy(行动 慢的，迟到的); retarded(智力迟钝的) v. 妨碍; 减速 【记】re反复, tard迟缓－妨碍 【参】tardy(adj 缓慢的); retarded(adj 智力迟钝的) 【类】divert: shunt = retard: brake转轨用来转向 = 刹车用来减速 【反】speed up(加速); accelerate(v 加速); expedite(v 加速); catalyze(v 催化; 促进); precipitate(v 促成) 【记】re + tardy 迟缓的；音：拖的，邋的，拖邋 【相关】bastard 私生子 和retard口语中是骂人的话 retard (v.)  late 15c., ""make slow or slower,"" from French retarder ""restrain, hold (someone) back, keep (someone from doing something); come to a stop"" (13c.) or directly from Latin retardare ""make slow, delay, keep back, hinder"" (see retardation). Related: Retarded; retarding. The noun is recorded from 1788 in the sense ""retardation, delay;"" from 1970 in offensive meaning ""retarded person,"" originally American English, with accent on first syllable. Other words used for ""one who is mentally retarded"" include retardate (1956), retardee (1971)."
